Returns a mutable reference to the last item in the vector, or
`None` if it is empty.

# Examples

Basic usage:

```
#![feature(vec_peek_mut)]
let mut vec = Vec::new();
assert!(vec.peek_mut().is_none());

vec.push(1);
vec.push(5);
vec.push(2);
assert_eq!(vec.last(), Some(&2));
if let Some(mut val) = vec.peek_mut() {
    *val = 0;
}
assert_eq!(vec.last(), Some(&0));
```
